               <head>Petition</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of ʿArz̤ah dāsht</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85064905 http://lccn.loc.gov/n50002518 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85064915" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Or_16933_18-item1">
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21853">ʿArz̤ah dāsht</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21853">عرضه داشت</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Petition to unnamed royal addressee (with chatr) by Mr Major (?) stating that matters of state have repeatedly been submitted. However, the matter of the drought and famine (qaḥaṭ [va] makhmaṣah) affecting this country (īn dayār) has not been expedited. As a result, many corpses/carcasses are evident in villages. Writer only able to amass the amount of 200,000 rps with extreme difficulty; deposited in the kothi of Jagat Seth, Khvushhal Chand, and Maharajah Udot Chand. A portion is dispatched with Budh Singh, the vakīl of Maharajah Shitab Ray Bahadur Mansurjang. Concludes with a prayer for the addressee (i.e. Emperor Shāh ʿĀlam) </p>
                        <p>Not dated </p>
                        <p>Narrow text panel of light zar afshānī or gold spray over a pale tinted ground; 2 upper cartouches (invocation and title) painted in gold; gold painted and dimpled chatr above title cartouche; sar lawḥ above text panel in shape of low arch, filled with symmetrical scrolling floral ornament; painted gold floral motifs in diaper, scale-like matrix on plain paper ground; narrow outer border; angled corner (bottom right) </p>
                        <p>Bonhams, Knightsbridge, Sale 22524 (5 Nov 2014, 10:30), Lot 18 </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
